### Command

build

### Is this a regression?

- [X] Yes, this behavior used to work in the previous version

### The previous version in which this bug was not present was

v17

### Description

Background: Mostly vanilla angular application using PWA since Angular ~5 doing normal `ng update`s.

Service worker only being used for caching static assets and serving them offline

---

When upgrading to v18 I accepted the migration to `:application` - the schematic did not migrate the `build.configurations.production.serviceWorker` from a boolean (`true`)

```
ng serve --proxy-config proxy-dev.conf.json  --configuration production
Error: Schema validation failed with the following errors:
  Data path "/serviceWorker" must be string.
  Data path "/serviceWorker" must be equal to constant.
  Data path "/serviceWorker" must match exactly one schema in oneOf.
```

Through trial and error I discovered the "correct"  new value for the `build.configurations.production.serviceWorker` field: `ngsw-config.json` (aside -- FR: link the schema from [the migration docs](https://angular.dev/tools/cli/build-system-migration)? üôè)

The service worker appeared to fetch and serve assets as expected **but** just before promoting from canary to prod I did an extra QA pass (it was sus that my `angular.json` wasn't properly migrated) and discovered that refreshing while offline now reported a 504

![Screenshot_20240818_113433](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/34ba9b97-6140-49e7-a469-215318d4aa48)

The above 504 is being served from the Service Worker and it appears the handling logic isn't serving the cached copy on network error anymore.

* ‚õî Running my v18 build locally with `ng serve --configuration production` shared the same issue
* ‚úÖ Reverting to v17 and it again worked as expected.
* ‚úÖ Making a new v18 build with `angular.json` reverted to the v17 version (using `:build` rather than `:application`) works as expected when using `ng serve --configuration production`
* ‚õî Making a new v18 build with the reverted `angular.json` and substituting `:build` for `:build-esbuild` failed to register any service worker 
  * This seems like a separate issue, the `:application` build does still register the SW and serve assets

### Minimal Reproduction

I assume (but have not tested) this would affect any PWA-enabled repo upgraded from v17 to v18 which performs the migration.

I have a workaround that allows me to upgrade to v18 (using the old & busted webpack builder)

